    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Headcloths, often of fine fabric, worn wrapped around a woman's head and usually tied on top of the head, often with ends hanging loose; worn as part of women's traditional dress in West Africa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
